<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1694,2046]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="448" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1946,1973]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A small (wingspan 
<quantity box="[551,675,1947,1974]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13 mm</quantity>
) uniformly lemon yellow species with light brown pattern from ⅓ of dorsal margin towards base of the forewing to its mid width (
<figureCitation box="[867,997,1983,2009]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–28" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1800,1825]" captionTargetBox="[245,1342,166,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[245,1342,166,1780]" captionText="FIGURES 13–28. Adults of Ancylosis spp. 13–14. A. roscidella. 15. A. oblitella. 16–17. A. sabulosella. 18-19. A. deserticola. 20–21. A. leucocephala. 22. A. rhodochrella. 23. A. hellenica. 24–28. A. larissae sp. nov. 13. ♀, Crimea. Prep. no. 26/19. 14. ♀, Crimea. Prep. no. 33/19. 15. ♀, Donetsk &amp; Zaporizhzhia reg. 16. ♂, Luhansk reg. Prep. no. 070.18. 17. ♂, Lectotype, Naryn. 18. ♀, Kyiv reg. Prep. no. 076.18. 19. ♂, Syntype. Sarepta. Prep. no. 4227 U. Roesler. 20. ♂, Zhamansai. 21. ♂, Holotype, Naryn. Prep. no. 4234 U. Roesler. 22. ♀, Hadjin. Prep. no. 57/19. 23. ♂, Beyrut. Prep. no. 56/19. 24. ♀, Paratype. Crimea. Prep. no. 34/19. 25. ♂, Paratype. Crimea. Prep. no. 36/19. 26. ♂, Paratype. Crimea (photo F. Graf). 27. ♀, Holotype. Crimea. Prep. no. 29/19. 28. ♂, Paratype. Crimea. Prep. no. 32/19. Scale bar: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3444592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3444592/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">Figs 16, 17</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chretien, 1911)" authorityName="Chretien" authorityYear="1911" baseAuthorityName="Chretien" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[1017,1436,1983,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limoniella">
<emphasis box="[1017,1246,1983,2009]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="447">Ancylosis limoniella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chretien, P." box="[1260,1428,1983,2009]" pageId="10" pageNumber="447" pagination="33 - 36" refId="ref24021" refString="Chretien, P. (1911) Description de nouvelles especes de Phycides de Mauritanie (Lep.). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 2, 33 - 36." type="journal article" year="1911">Chrétien, 1911</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is very similar externally but it is slightly lighter. The distinctly bulged ventral margin of valva, the large subcostal hump and bend aedeagus are characteristic for the male genitalia. The culcita with broadly bugled anterior margin and with long narrow anterior projection is characteristic too (
<figureCitation box="[854,939,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–38" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[202,1386,166,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[202,1386,166,1907]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 33–38. Male genitalia of Ancylosis spp. 33–34. A. albicosta. 35. A. oblitella. 36. A. cinnamomella. 37. A. roscidella. 38. A. sabulosella. 33. Kherson reg. Prep. no. 114/17. 34. Syntype. Prep. no. 4226 U. Roesler. 35. Kyiv reg. Prep. no. 083.18. 36. Crimea. Prep. no. 068.18. 37. Zaporizhzhia reg. Prep. no. 287/18. 38. Luhansk reg. Prep. no. 070.18. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3371930/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chretien" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[959,1188,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limoniella">
<emphasis box="[959,1188,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Ancylosis limoniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the apically broader valva, the absence of subcostal hump and pointed apically uncus. The female genitalia are characterized by long antrum, zigzag curved ductus bursae and corpus bursae with rounded distal portion. For the differences from related species see below under the description of the female genitalia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,332,359]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Biology.</emphasis>
Host plant is unknown. In 
<collectingCountry box="[612,702,333,359]" name="Ukraine" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
the single male was attracted to light in steppe habitats in July. However, we suggest the occurance this species in adjacent calcerous habitats.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,404,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[360,435,405,431]" name="Russia" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Russia</collectingCountry>
(Stavropolskiy kray, Volga region, Southern Ural) (
<bibRefCitation author="Sinev, S. Yu." box="[1016,1149,405,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="156 - 170" refId="ref27289" refString="Sinev, S. Yu. (2008) Pyralidae. In: Sinev, S. Yu. (Ed.), Catalogue of the Lepidoptera of Russia, KMK Scientific Press Ltd., St. Petersburg-Moskow, pp. 156 - 170. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2008">Sinev 2008</bibRefCitation>
), North-West 
<collectingCountry box="[1306,1437,405,431]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(Uralsk, Indersky), 
<collectingCountry box="[372,530,441,467]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[541,670,441,467]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[682,813,441,467]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[823,963,441,467]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[975,1073,441,467]" name="Pakistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1085,1133,441,467]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1254,441,467]" name="Mongolia" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Roesler, R. - U." box="[1269,1423,441,467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref26862" refString="Roesler, R. - U. (1973) Phycitinae. Trifine Acrobasiina. In: Amsel, H. G., Gregor, F. &amp; Reisser, H. (Eds.), Microlepidoptera Palaearctica, 4 (1 - 2), Georg Fromme &amp; Co., Wien. Part 1, i-xvi, 1 - 752 pp., part 2, 1 - 137 pp., pls. 1 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1973">Roesler 1973</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,477,503]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">China</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[262,352,477,503]" name="Ukraine" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
the species is known from 
<collectingRegion box="[659,834,477,503]" country="Ukraine" name="Luhans'k" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Luhansk region</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bidzilya, O. V. &amp; Budashkin, Yu. I." box="[849,1169,477,503]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="59 - 67" refId="ref22877" refString="Bidzilya, O. V. &amp; Budashkin, Yu. I. (2004) New records of Lepidoptera from Ukraine. Proceedings of Zoological Museum of Kiev Taras Shevchenko National University, 2, 59 - 67. [in Ukrainian]" type="journal article" year="2004">Bidzilya &amp; Budashkin 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,513,539]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[321,543,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis box="[321,543,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Myelois sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on one male and three females from Narün (Naryn) (
<collectingRegion country="Kazakhstan" name="Atyrau Oblysy" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Atyrau region</collectingRegion>
, NW 
<collectingCountry box="[297,433,549,576]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
). One specimen from the type series without abdomen is kept in MfN (
<figureCitation box="[1276,1363,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–28" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1800,1825]" captionTargetBox="[245,1342,166,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[245,1342,166,1780]" captionText="FIGURES 13–28. Adults of Ancylosis spp. 13–14. A. roscidella. 15. A. oblitella. 16–17. A. sabulosella. 18-19. A. deserticola. 20–21. A. leucocephala. 22. A. rhodochrella. 23. A. hellenica. 24–28. A. larissae sp. nov. 13. ♀, Crimea. Prep. no. 26/19. 14. ♀, Crimea. Prep. no. 33/19. 15. ♀, Donetsk &amp; Zaporizhzhia reg. 16. ♂, Luhansk reg. Prep. no. 070.18. 17. ♂, Lectotype, Naryn. 18. ♀, Kyiv reg. Prep. no. 076.18. 19. ♂, Syntype. Sarepta. Prep. no. 4227 U. Roesler. 20. ♂, Zhamansai. 21. ♂, Holotype, Naryn. Prep. no. 4234 U. Roesler. 22. ♀, Hadjin. Prep. no. 57/19. 23. ♂, Beyrut. Prep. no. 56/19. 24. ♀, Paratype. Crimea. Prep. no. 34/19. 25. ♂, Paratype. Crimea. Prep. no. 36/19. 26. ♂, Paratype. Crimea (photo F. Graf). 27. ♀, Holotype. Crimea. Prep. no. 29/19. 28. ♂, Paratype. Crimea. Prep. no. 32/19. Scale bar: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3444592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3444592/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). This specimen was designated as a 
<typeStatus box="[496,599,585,611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">lectotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Korb, S." box="[643,835,584,611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="516 - 526" refId="ref25472" refString="Korb, S. (2017) Les types primaires de Pyraloidea de la collection Staudinger, conservee au Museum fur Naturkunde de Berlin (Leibniz-Institut fur Evolutions- und Biodiversitatsforschung). Alexanor, 27 (8), 516 - 526." type="journal article" year="2017">Korb (2017: 523</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 17). The rest specimens from the type series are not traced in the collection of MfN. Roesler figured the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[993,1154,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis box="[993,1154,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,288,657,683]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
and the female genitalia from the 
<typeStatus box="[687,785,657,683]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ragonot &amp; Hampson, 1901" authorityName="Ragonot &amp; Hampson" authorityYear="1901" box="[826,1308,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decolorella">
<emphasis box="[826,986,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. decolorella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ragonot, E. L. &amp; Hampson, G. F." box="[995,1308,657,683]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="1 - 602" refId="ref26565" refString="Ragonot, E. L. &amp; Hampson, G. F. (1901) Monographie des Phycitinae et des Galleriinae. In: Romanoff, N. M. Memoires sur les Lepidopteres, 8. St. Petersburg, pp. i-xli, 1 - 602., pls. 24 - 57." type="book chapter" year="1901">Ragonot &amp; Hampson, 1901</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Margilan (
<collectingCountry box="[224,357,693,720]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
). We studied male and female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[745,906,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis box="[745,906,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected sympatrically in 
<collectingCountry box="[1217,1358,693,719]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
. These specimens are similar externally to specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[728,818,729,755]" name="Ukraine" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
and undoubtedly are conspecific to the 
<typeStatus box="[1271,1374,729,755]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ragonot &amp; Hampson" authorityYear="1901" box="[293,534,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decolorella">
<emphasis box="[293,534,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Ancylosis decolorella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs both externally (
<bibRefCitation author="Ragonot, E. L. &amp; Hampson, G. F." box="[803,1108,765,791]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="1 - 602" refId="ref26565" refString="Ragonot, E. L. &amp; Hampson, G. F. (1901) Monographie des Phycitinae et des Galleriinae. In: Romanoff, N. M. Memoires sur les Lepidopteres, 8. St. Petersburg, pp. i-xli, 1 - 602., pls. 24 - 57." type="book chapter" year="1901">Ragonot &amp; Hampson 1901</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 42, fig. 14) and in the female genitalia from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[374,531,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis box="[374,531,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and considered as a separate species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Ragonot &amp; Hampson, 1901" authorityName="Ragonot &amp; Hampson" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decolorella">
<emphasis box="[949,1189,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Ancylosis decolorella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ragonot, E. L. &amp; Hampson, G. F." pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="1 - 602" refId="ref26565" refString="Ragonot, E. L. &amp; Hampson, G. F. (1901) Monographie des Phycitinae et des Galleriinae. In: Romanoff, N. M. Memoires sur les Lepidopteres, 8. St. Petersburg, pp. i-xli, 1 - 602., pls. 24 - 57." type="book chapter" year="1901">Ragonot &amp; Hampson, 1901</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[214,444,837,863]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">spec. rev., stat. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" box="[199,1033,873,899]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[467,626,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis box="[467,626,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are described here for the first time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,599,908,935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
Female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[436,599,908,935]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[436,599,908,935]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[615,699,909,936]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–62" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1934,1959]" captionTargetBox="[199,1388,166,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[199,1388,166,1915]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 59–62. Female genitalia of Ancylosis spp. 59. A. albicosta. 60. A. cinnamomella. 61. A. sabulosella. 62. A. oblitella. 59. Sarepta. Prep. no. 259/17. 60. Kyiv reg. Prep. no. 082.18. 61. Kandahar. Prep. no. 118/19. 62. Donetsk &amp; Zaporizhzhia reg. Prep. no. 074.18. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3371940/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales subovate, densely covered with long hairs; both apophyses straight, twice as long as the length of segment VIII; segment VIII as broad as long, tergum VIII with broad V-shaped posteromedial emargination extending anteriorely to about ⅔ length, anterior margin nearly straight with a very weak medial projecting, band-shaped, sternum VIII weakly sclerotized except lateral area; ductus bursae comparatively broad, twice as long as corpus bursae, zigzag curved in proximal portion, with longitudinal folds in distal portion, colliculum very short, antrum long, tubular, weakly broadend posteriorely, with transverse ringshaped sclerite at base, ductus seminalis very slender, arises from the end of ductus bursae before the beginning of colliculum; corpus bursae elongated, pear-shaped, signa long, narrow, thorn shaped with small rounded basal plate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[466,625,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis box="[466,625,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chretien" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[836,981,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limoniella">
<emphasis box="[836,981,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. limoniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but segment VIII is shorter, subquadrate rather than subrectangular, antrum and ductus bursae are longer. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ragonot &amp; Hampson, 1901)" authorityName="Ragonot &amp; Hampson" authorityYear="1901" baseAuthorityName="Ragonot &amp; Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbrilimbella">
<emphasis box="[894,1169,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Ancylosis umbrilimbella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ragonot, E. L. &amp; Hampson, G. F." pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="1 - 602" refId="ref26565" refString="Ragonot, E. L. &amp; Hampson, G. F. (1901) Monographie des Phycitinae et des Galleriinae. In: Romanoff, N. M. Memoires sur les Lepidopteres, 8. St. Petersburg, pp. i-xli, 1 - 602., pls. 24 - 57." type="book chapter" year="1901">Ragonot &amp; Hampson, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
differs in the broader, funnel-shaped rather than tubular antrum, longer segment VIII, thicker apophysis anterioris and smaller signa in the distal portion of the bursae copulatrix (
<bibRefCitation author="Roesler, R. - U." box="[925,1080,1341,1367]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref26862" refString="Roesler, R. - U. (1973) Phycitinae. Trifine Acrobasiina. In: Amsel, H. G., Gregor, F. &amp; Reisser, H. (Eds.), Microlepidoptera Palaearctica, 4 (1 - 2), Georg Fromme &amp; Co., Wien. Part 1, i-xvi, 1 - 752 pp., part 2, 1 - 137 pp., pls. 1 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1973">Roesler 1973</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 133, fig. 172).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1377,1403]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Notes.</emphasis>
The record of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ragonot &amp; Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[445,636,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbrilimbella">
<emphasis box="[445,636,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. umbrilimbella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[708,775,1377,1403]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ren, Y." box="[791,1019,1377,1403]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="288 - 417" refId="ref26622" refString="Ren, Y. (2012) Phycitinae. In: Li, H. H. (Ed.), Microlepidoptera of Qinling Mountains. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 288 - 417." type="book chapter" year="2012">Ren 2012: 399–400</bibRefCitation>
, figs 256; pl. 11, fig. 256) should be referred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1879" box="[276,435,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis box="[276,435,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="448" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[199,441,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosella">
<emphasis box="[199,441,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">Ancylosis sabulosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chretien" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[454,599,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limoniella">
<emphasis box="[454,599,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. limoniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Roesler, 1970" authorityName="Roesler" authorityYear="1970" box="[612,924,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syriopsidis">
<emphasis box="[612,763,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. syriopsidis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Roesler, R. - U." box="[770,924,1449,1475]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="35 - 105" refId="ref26811" refString="Roesler, R. - U. (1970) Die trifinen Phycitinae. Ergebnisse der zoologischen Forschungen von Dr. Z. Kaszab in der Mongolei (Lepidoptera, Pyralidae). Reichenbachia, 13 (7), 35 - 105., figs. 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1970">Roesler, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Caradja, 1937)" authorityName="Caradja" authorityYear="1937" baseAuthorityName="Caradja" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[978,1305,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steppicola">
<emphasis box="[978,1123,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="448">A. steppicola</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Caradja, A. &amp; Meyrick, E." box="[1137,1297,1449,1475]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="137 - 182" refId="ref23984" refString="Caradja, A. &amp; Meyrick, E. (1937) Materialien zu einer Mikrolepidopterenfauna des Yulingshanmassivs (Provinz Yunnan). Deutsche entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 51 (4), 137 - 182." type="journal article" year="1937">Caradja, 1937</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
have rather similar wing pattern. 
<bibRefCitation author="Roesler, R. - U." box="[389,612,1485,1511]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref26862" refString="Roesler, R. - U. (1973) Phycitinae. Trifine Acrobasiina. In: Amsel, H. G., Gregor, F. &amp; Reisser, H. (Eds.), Microlepidoptera Palaearctica, 4 (1 - 2), Georg Fromme &amp; Co., Wien. Part 1, i-xvi, 1 - 752 pp., part 2, 1 - 137 pp., pls. 1 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1973">Roesler (1973: 410)</bibRefCitation>
followed 
<bibRefCitation author="Amsel, H. G." box="[723,934,1485,1512]" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" pagination="224 - 237" refId="ref22364" refString="Amsel, H. G. (1942) Revision der Gattung Holcopogon Stgr. (Lepidoptera: Scythrididae). Veroffentlichungen aus dem Deutschen Kolonial- und Ubersee-Museum in Bremen, 3, 224 - 237., pl. 3." type="journal article" year="1942">Amsel (1942: 226)</bibRefCitation>
considering such cases as a convergence. He mentioned that species from this group can easily be separated by the venation and other external characters which are diagnostic for the subgenera of 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Roesler (1973)" authorityName="sensu Roesler" authorityYear="1973" box="[545,898,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Ancylosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
